<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10531&amp;p=118607#p118607"><![CDATA[
There are so called 'CPU simulators', like a 6502 simulator, that allow to enter and run a snippet of code. However, they are not tied to any particular hardware like NES. So if you want to debug NES-related code, you just have to use a NES emulator.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Tue Sep 24, 2013 6:56 am</p><hr />
